title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION SYSTEM BUILDING

description.narrative: Support relevant government institutions to develop and implement laws, regulatory frameworks and service delivery systems in place to adequately improve children's access to justice and birth registration services, which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: South Sudanese Children and young people at risk of violence, exploitation and abuse, in emergency and non-emergency settings, use integrated basic social services

title.narrative: Support relevant government institutions to develop and implement laws, regulatory frameworks and service delivery systems in placeto adequately improve children?s access to justice and birth registration services

description.narrative: As a result of UNICEF support, key results have been demonstrated in children’s access to justice and birth registration services as 37,321 people ( 15,603 boys, ;18,795 girls ;1,544 women, 1,379 men) were reached with messages on children&39;s rights. In total, 356 children and youth (118 girls) had access to at least one justice service consistent with the best interest of the child and youth; 561 children and youth (191 girls) accessed case management services including MHPSS, FTR and referrals; and 71,229 children (35,699 girls) were reached with birth notification services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
